The article discusses the digital gender gap and the launch of USAID's WomenConnect Challenge, an initiative aimed at closing the gap. It states that over a billion and a half women in low- and middle-income countries still do not own mobile phones, and the gap in internet use between men and women has been increasing. The article emphasizes the importance of closing this gap, as it can help women lift their families out of poverty and become active participants in their societies. The WomenConnect Challenge will identify and test pilot approaches to closing the gender digital divide, and then scale proven solutions for maximum impact. The article also highlights the Trump Administration's efforts to empower women and expand their economic opportunities.